cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference this project, please cite it as below."
title: "GG Tank Watch: an AI-assisted information conduit for a chemical-tank emergency"
abstract: >-
  A single-page emergency-information dashboard built downwind of the May 2026
  Garden Grove (California) methyl-methacrylate tank evacuation. It is a pure
  information conduit: it amplifies and timestamps official and news sources and
  routes every protective-action decision back to the responsible authority,
  authoring no hazard verdicts of its own. An LLM gathers facts; deterministic
  Python enforces corroboration, provenance, freshness, and date-sanity gates at
  a single validation chokepoint before anything is published. The repository is
  a frozen archive of the build and its safety and design decisions, kept behind
  a pre-distribution (attorney) review gate.
type: software
